\title{MPM: Matrix Population Models for Stage-Structured Populations in R}
\description{
Provides tools for constructing and comparing age- and stage-based matrix
population models (MPMs). Implements three methods for handling stage
duration, when stages are defined in terms of age:
}
\details{
\itemize{
\item \strong{AAS} (Asymptotic Age-within Stage): iterative method described by Kendall et al. 2019.
\item \strong{FAS} (Fixed Age within Stage): simple but biased method, included for
legacy comparisons.
\item \strong{Unroll}: converts age-based stages into a full age-based Leslie
matrix, supporting variable stage durations and within-stage survival
ramps.
}

